[SN]TITLE[SN]
World Cup 2014: Switzerland's Steve von Bergen heads home

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Switzerland defender Steve von Bergen has been ruled out of the World Cup after breaking a cheekbone in the 5-2 defeat by France.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Von Bergen had blood pouring from a cut under his eye after he was accidently kicked in the face by France striker Olivier Giroud in the sixth minute.
The 31-year-old was taken to hospital in Salvador.
Young Boys Berne centre-half Von Bergen will now return to Switzerland to receive treatment from specialists.
